Data Munging¶

In [48]:
# Grouping data by subset of time period 
Sub1 = export[export["Year"].isin([2006, 2007,2008, 2009, 2010])]
Sub2 = export[export["Year"].isin([2011, 2012, 2013, 2014, 2015])]
Sub3 = export[export["Year"].isin([2016, 2017, 2018, 2019, 2020])]
In [49]:
# Dropping year column for easier manipulation
Sub1_1 = Sub1.drop(['Year'], axis=1)
Sub2_2 = Sub2.drop(['Year'], axis=1)
Sub3_3 = Sub3.drop(['Year'], axis=1)
In [50]:
# Grouping the data again without year column to group trade value by partners of time period 
df1 = Sub1_1.groupby(['Exporter','Exporter ISO3','Exporter region','Importer','Importer ISO3','Importer region'],
                    as_index=False).agg({'Trade_Value': 'sum'})

df2 = Sub2_2.groupby(['Exporter','Exporter ISO3','Exporter region','Importer','Importer ISO3'],
                    as_index=False).agg({'Trade_Value': 'sum'})

df3 = Sub3_3.groupby(['Exporter','Exporter ISO3','Exporter region','Importer','Importer ISO3'],
                    as_index=False).agg({'Trade_Value': 'sum'})
In [51]:
# Dropping countries that dont appear on wm dataframe 
df1 = df1[df1['Exporter ISO3'] != 'MYT']
df1 = df1[df1['Importer ISO3'] != 'MYT']
df1 = df1[df1['Importer ISO3'] != 'TKL']
df1 = df1[df1['Importer ISO3'] != 'TKL']

df2 = df2[df2['Exporter ISO3'] != 'MYT']
df2 = df2[df2['Importer ISO3'] != 'MYT']
df2 = df2[df2['Exporter ISO3'] != 'TKL']
df2 = df2[df2['Importer ISO3'] != 'TKL']

df3 = df3[df3['Exporter ISO3'] != 'MYT']
df3 = df3[df3['Importer ISO3'] != 'MYT']
df3 = df3[df3['Exporter ISO3'] != 'TKL']
df3 = df3[df3['Importer ISO3'] != 'TKL']

# Removing zero trade values for easier network contstruction
df22 =df2[df2['Trade_Value']!=0]
df33 =df3[df3['Trade_Value']!=0]

Graph 1 2006-2010¶

In [52]:
# Constructing source and target and node value based on trade value 
graph1 = nx.from_pandas_edgelist(df1, source = 'Exporter ISO3', target = 'Importer ISO3',

                     edge_attr = 'Trade_Value',create_using = nx.DiGraph())

     pos[elem] = (mx[count], my[count])

In [201]:
# Plotting Map
plt.figure(figsize= [14,10])
# Adding basemap with features 
m = Basemap(projection='merc', llcrnrlat=-80, urcrnrlat=80, llcrnrlon=-180, urcrnrlon=180, epsg= 4326)
m.drawmapboundary(fill_color='aliceblue')
m.fillcontinents(color='lightgrey')
m.drawcoastlines(linewidth= 0.5)
m.drawcountries(linewidth = 0.5)

# Node aesthetic
node1 =nx.draw_networkx_nodes(G = graph1, pos = pos, 

                        node_color = node_color, alpha = 0.8, node_size = [v * 3 for v in d.values()])

# Edge aesthetic
edges1 = nx.draw_networkx_edges(G = graph1, pos = pos, edge_color='black',

                        alpha=0.1, arrows = False)
# Title, colobar adjument and saving to png
plt.title("Exports of Copper, Nickel and REEs from Sub-Saharan Africa between 2006 and 2010")
plt.colorbar(node1, shrink=0.5)
plt.savefig("NX2006_2010.png", format="PNG")
